  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will serve as a Full Time Site In-Charge, leading on-site operations to ensure safe, high-quality execution of tunneling works including Mined Tunnels and Cross Passages. You will collaborate closely with project teams to drive progress and uphold project standards.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead daily site operations to ensure timely and efficient work execution</li><li>Assisting the project manager at times in need </li><li>Apply knowledge of tunneling works such as Mined Tunnels and Cross Passages to oversee technical site activities</li><li>Conduct regular inspections of construction sites to identify and eliminate potential safety hazards, ensuring a safe working environment</li><li>Enforce site safety rules rigorously to minimize work-related accidents and injuries</li><li>Supervise sub-contractors and in-house workers to maintain productivity and quality standards</li><li>Collaborate with site operations staff to align work progress with the project schedule</li><li>Verify that installations are performed according to construction drawings to meet design specifications</li><li>Monitor work progress and quality continuously to ensure compliance with workmanship standards</li><li>Attend daily tool-box meetings and communicate clear, actionable instructions to the workforce</li><li>Ensure full understanding and compliance with project requirements and scope of work</li><li>Prepare detailed Daily Reports and Production Reports to document site activities and progress</li><li>Strong skills in interpreting and reading  drawings </li><li>Proficient in preparing Bar Bending Schedules (BBS) will be advantage </li><li>Must be knowledgeable in AutoCAD usage and functions</li><li>Fluent in English</li></ul>",
